Code 
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(forcats)
surveys <- read_csv(here("surveys.csv"))

1.reorder

Code 
surveys <- surveys|> 
  drop_na() |>
  mutate(species = factor(species), 
         weight = as.numeric(weight),
         species=fct_reorder(species, weight, .desc = TRUE))
Code 
ggplot(data=surveys, mapping=aes(x = weight, 
                                  y = species)) + 
  geom_jitter(color="tomato", alpha=.3) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0)+ 
  labs(y="",x="weight of rodentin grams", title = "Box plot for different species weights of rodents in grams across speices")

Code 
ggplot(data = surveys, 
       mapping = aes(x=year, y=weight, col = genus))+
  geom_line() +
  labs(y="", title = "Time plot of mean weight of genuses", col="Rodent Genus")

Code 
surveys <- surveys|> 
  group_by(year)|>
  mutate(mean_weight = mean(weight)) 

ggplot(surveys) +
  geom_line(aes(x=year, 
                y=mean_weight, 
                col=genus)) +
  labs(y="", 
       title = "Time plot of mean weight of genuses", col="Rodent Genus")

Code 
surveys <- surveys|> 
  mutate(species = factor(species), 
         mean_weight = as.numeric(mean_weight),
         species=fct_reorder(species, mean_weight, .desc = TRUE))
ggplot(surveys) +
  geom_line(aes(x=year,
                y=mean_weight,
                col=genus)) +
  labs(y="", 
       title = "Time plot of mean weight of genuses", 
       col="Rodent Genus")

Code 
nsurveys <- surveys |>
  mutate(day_of_week = factor(day_of_week),
         day_of_week = ordered(day_of_week, 
                                    c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", 
"Fri", "Sat", "Sun") )) |>
  drop_na(day_of_week)
ggplot(nsurveys, aes(x=day_of_week)) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(y="", title="Count of rodent caught")

Code 
surveys <- surveys |> 
  mutate(new=fct_collapse(day_of_week,
         Weekday = c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed","Thu", "Fri"),
         Weekend = c("Sat", "Sun"))) 
    
ggplot(surveys, aes(x=new)) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(y="", title="Count of rodents caught",x="Day of week")

```{r}
library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(forcats)
surveys <- read_csv(here("surveys.csv"))
```

1.reorder

```{r}
surveys <- surveys|> 
  drop_na() |>
  mutate(species = factor(species), 
         weight = as.numeric(weight),
         species=fct_reorder(species, weight, .desc = TRUE))
  
```

```{r}
ggplot(data=surveys, mapping=aes(x = weight, 
                                  y = species)) + 
  geom_jitter(color="tomato", alpha=.3) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.alpha = 0)+ 
  labs(y="",x="weight of rodentin grams", title = "Box plot for different species weights of rodents in grams across speices")
```

```{r}
ggplot(data = surveys, 
       mapping = aes(x=year, y=weight, col = genus))+
  geom_line() +
  labs(y="", title = "Time plot of mean weight of genuses", col="Rodent Genus")
```

```{r}
surveys <- surveys|> 
  group_by(year)|>
  mutate(mean_weight = mean(weight)) 

ggplot(surveys) +
  geom_line(aes(x=year, 
                y=mean_weight, 
                col=genus)) +
  labs(y="", 
       title = "Time plot of mean weight of genuses", col="Rodent Genus")
```

```{r}
surveys <- surveys|> 
  mutate(species = factor(species), 
         mean_weight = as.numeric(mean_weight),
         species=fct_reorder(species, mean_weight, .desc = TRUE))
ggplot(surveys) +
  geom_line(aes(x=year,
                y=mean_weight,
                col=genus)) +
  labs(y="", 
       title = "Time plot of mean weight of genuses", 
       col="Rodent Genus") 
   
```

```{r}
nsurveys <- surveys |>
  mutate(day_of_week = factor(day_of_week),
         day_of_week = ordered(day_of_week, 
                                    c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", 
"Fri", "Sat", "Sun") )) |>
  drop_na(day_of_week)
ggplot(nsurveys, aes(x=day_of_week)) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(y="", title="Count of rodent caught")
```

```{r}
surveys <- surveys |> 
  mutate(new=fct_collapse(day_of_week,
         Weekday = c("Mon", "Tue", "Wed","Thu", "Fri"),
         Weekend = c("Sat", "Sun"))) 
    
ggplot(surveys, aes(x=new)) +
  geom_bar() +
  labs(y="", title="Count of rodents caught",x="Day of week")
```
